    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-05T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-05T20:00:00-05:00" n="310"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94/2255: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-06T10:00:00+09:00"
                            >September 6, 1941—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 6—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1406. For the Secretary and the Under Secretary only. Broadcasts from American
                    stations during the past few days continue to stress in various ways that “Japan
                    has surrendered to the United States”. As press and radio comment of this
                    character is likely to become known here, especially among military and naval
                    circles, in spite of the censorship, I venture to refer to the Embassy’s 1355,
                    August 30, 6 p.m., paragraph 7, in the hope that the Administration may wish to
                    give the American press and radio a “leader” tending to counterbalance publicity
                    which might seriously prejudice the success of the current conversations with
                    the Japanese Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
